        "definition": "Graphical method plotting 1/v versus 1/[S] to linearize Michaelis–Menten data and determine Km and Vmax from intercepts and slope.",
        "summary": "Lineweaver–Burk plots yield a straight line with y-intercept 1/Vmax and x-intercept −1/Km. Inhibitor effects appear as characteristic changes in slope and intercepts."
