      "content": {
        "title": "Mixed and Uncompetitive Inhibition",
        "definition": "Mixed inhibition alters both Km and Vmax; uncompetitive inhibition binds only ES complex, decreasing both parameters proportionally with parallel Lineweaver-Burk lines.",
        "summary": "Uncompetitive inhibition rare in drugs but tested conceptually. Mixed is general case of noncompetitive binding."
      },
